member.summary: The DOM document model domain to set to get around Coss Site Scripting problems in web browsers. If the Mashup page is located on another server than the one the Web Player is installed on, the domain property of the Mashup and the Web Player pages must be changed so that they match. summary.para: The ApiFileHandler class is used to create the Java Script API (.js) file. The JS API can have "<%# XX.YY %>" tags that is replaced by the return value of the property YY of class/instance XX in the Metadata. The substitution is done using Metadata.GetFunctionName(XX.YY). The JavScript API can also contain "ifdef"-like statements to remove code from earlier versions of the API.

#APINEW X.Y ... code #ENDAPI
the X.Y is the version where the new functionallity is added.

The code can also contain tags for code that is removed from a specific version and forward (deprecated code).
#APIREMOVE X.Y ... code #ENDAPI

member.name: M:Spotfire.Dxp.Web.InternalDocumentCacheEntry.CloningFinished(System.Boolean)
member.summary:
This method should be called when a calling cloner has finished its work. The method releases the thread lock on this object, for example Informs waiting threads that it is now OK to start working with this instance. It also decreases the counter for pending clones.
If the property
is not set when this method is called, the next thread accessing the object should not wait for the property to be set. Instead interrupt the wait and let that second thread try to set the property.
If false the nr of instances that has cloned this template will be decreased.

member.name: T:Spotfire.Dxp.Web.Utilities.Identifier
member.summary: Internal static class used to create unique identifier strings.
member.remarks: This class is used to create unique IDs in three different formats: 1. use the Guid.NewGuid() method to construct a new Guid instance. That Guid is rendered as a string prefixed with a random character ranging from a-f and with the node information stripped making the identifier string 21 characters long. 2. use NextNodeId in the WebAnalysis to get a unique integer for the current WebAnalysis, the id will be id_ where _ is an integer. 3. The unique integer is available only when the node is inserted in the web document. If this is still not the case, a temporary string notSet is used. This is of course not unique, but later this string will be replaced by an id of type 2.

member.summary: A temporarily set identifier string. The id is supposed to be replaced when the web document node is inserted in the web document using NewIdentifier(WebAnalysis wa)

member.returns: A string representing a unique identifier.

member.name: M:Spotfire.Dxp.Web.Utilities.Identifier.NewIdentifier(Spotfire.Dxp.Web.WebAnalysis)
member.summary: A new identifier string constructed based on the position on the web document tree. The reason for this, instead of using a Guid is that a specific web document node should have the same Id every time an analysis is loaded. This property is very useful for debugging and performance testing based on recorded sessions compared to a new run.
member.param: The WebAnalysis keeping the highest id number used so far.
member.returns: A string representing a unique identifier.
